messages.content: Idk how the bot messed that one up
Anyway, you can play it multiple times in a row and just stay in the ultimate stance for the rest of the fight which is quite something
no, it just used alchemise

It's a very good tool for ending short and medium length fights. Gives you that quick burst of damage, and immediately puts you into ultimate stance. You want to pair it with lots of cheap skills to proc the skill bonuses quickly, and finishers to reset the counter on skill bonuses. A perfect card for fights where you need to burst stuff down quickly like reptomancer or tri slavers. You do want to make sure you take a few extra ways to re-enter stances, as this will leave you without any stance on the following turn (in fights that go long like giant head or most bosses). Don't get too overconfident when this is wrecking the short and medium fights, you need to still be on the lookout for scaling solutions for longer fights, especially neow. If you can find 2-3 of these and strange spoon, that's probably pretty excellent.
